# Graybox Editor Conventions

## Architecture

- **Single responsibility**: one file = one concern. Never mix UI rendering with 3D logic or file I/O.
- **Store slices** live in `src/store/` — `editorStore`, `objectStore`, `selectionStore`, `toolStore`.
- **Three.js modules** live in `src/three/` — each has a `create___()` factory function.
- **Shared styles** live in `src/styles/theme.ts`. Never define button/input styles inline per-component.
- **Constants** live in `src/constants.ts`. Never hardcode colors, thresholds, or sizes.

## Object Mutations & Undo

- ALL object changes must go through the Command pattern (undo/redo stack).
- For continuous drags (gizmo, extrude), use `beginBatch()` / `commitBatch()` to group into one undo step.
- `updateObject` is the low-level setter; always wrap it in a Command for undoable operations.

## Adding a New Primitive

1. Add the type to `PrimitiveType` in `src/types.ts`
2. Add geometry creation in `src/three/primitiveGeometry.ts`
3. Add the name mapping in `src/utils/naming.ts`
4. Add palette button in `src/components/PrimitivePalette.tsx`

## Exports

- All 3D export logic (GLTF, OBJ, FBX) lives in `src/three/exporters.ts`.
- Download helper lives in `src/utils/download.ts` — no duplicates.
- Export always uses the live viewport scene (clone meshes), never reconstructs geometry.

## Code Style

- No inline `style={{}}` — use shared style objects from `src/styles/theme.ts`.
- No magic numbers — import from `src/constants.ts`.
- No `as any` — use proper typing or explicit casts with comments.
- Respond in Korean to the user.
